args: Aw, ham hocks! We got so wrapped up in\nour fiend huntin', we didn't realize how\ndeep into the labyrinth we were gettin'!
Yeah, I don't like this.\nLet's hurry and find a way out.
Agreed. But we still need to proceed\nwith caution.
Right. They say these sorts of ruins\nare teeming with traps.
Oh please! Which of us is stupid enough\nto go wanderin' into a tra—
Sweet corn casserole! A whole buncha\narrows just shot outta the damn walls!
Fine work answering your own question,\nRanzal.
The arrows aren't stopping!\nWe're going to have to make\na run for...
Wait, now the WALLS are closing in?!
I don't wanna be a Ranzal sandwich!\nSomebody do somethin' already!
Are introductions really more important\nthan NOT being crushed?!
No, but how did you get in here?\nI don't see a single entrance or egress!
Ah! A passage just opened in the wall!

Whew! Looks like we're in the clear.
I ain't never eatin' a sandwich again!
Well, unless it's tasty. Or I'm hungry.
Or if it's one'a those pickle and banana—
So the walls were designed to open with\nthe proper incantation? Fascinating.
Thanks, friend. Ya really saved our\nhides back there.
Heh. That remains to be seen. Before you\ntake another step, look at the floor.
Hmm. Some patches of soil appear to be\na different color.
Are ya kiddin' me?! MORE traps?\nI almost tromped right on that puppy!
Yes, and there's plenty more where that\ncame from. So stay close to me if you\nwant to remain in one piece.
Are you some kind of scholar?
Scholar? Not quite. I'm the world's\ngreatest treasure hunter!\nName's Marty, by the way.
Thanks to you, Marty.\nWe really owe you one.
It's like yer some kinda trap whisperer!\nHow'd ya know exactly what to do\nevery step'a the way?
Wouldn't be much of a treasure hunter\nif I didn't have a knack for such things.
Interesting. I don't suppose you'd\nconsider joining us while we hunt\nfiends in the rui—
Nope! Big nope. Sorry, friend,\nbut I'm not a tour guide.
My destiny is treasure, and treasure is my\ndestiny. I have a duty to wow the world by\nbringing all of its secrets into the light!
But also noble, in its way. Forgive me.\nI shouldn't have asked you to abandon that.
No you should not have! So what say you\nmake it up to me: Got any juicy leads on\ntreasure that I can have? Hmmmmmmm?
I've already cleaned this place out, see?\nNeed a new line of investigation.
You cleaned it out completely? Wow.
I wish I had something to share, but...
What about the old maps in the Halidom?
Er, the Halidom has old maps?

Our treasure vault is stuffed to the gills
with dusty old maps and atlases.
The Founder himself left them there,
so they must be of some significance.
Wait. You have maps that belonged to\nthe Founder? Those are treasures even if\nthey DON'T have big red X's on them!
But if they DO have red X's... Hoo hoo!\nLady, you know JUST how to tickle a man's\ntreasure-lust.
Right then! Lead the way to this ＂Halidom＂!\nWait, never mind—I already have a good\nidea where it is. Follow me!

Boy, this guy is a real laugh riot.
We'll show ya the way, pal—just
give us a minute so we can...
Huh?! How'd he get so far ahead?
Do you think we can trust him,\n{player_name}?
We can trust his ＂treasure-lust,＂\nif nothing else.
Hey! Are you coming, or am I keeping all\nthose sweet, voluminous maps for myself?\nHoo hoo hoooooo!
